18/09/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- The government decided on Wednesday (September 17th) to ask parliament to extend the mandate for cross-border military operations against the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in northern Iraq by a year.
The current mandate expires on October 17th.
In other news Wednesday, an earthquake measuring 4.7 on the Richter scale rattled the eastern province of Erzincan.
Authorities reported no injuries, but there was minor damage.
(Zaman, Hurriyet - 18/09/08;
Anadolu news agency, Reuters, AP, AFP, CNN Turk, Hurriyet - 17/09/08)
